title: Independent candidate Amjad Ali wins PK-07 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): The Independent candidate Amjad Ali has won the Khyber Pakhtunkhwa Assembly election from PK-07, Swat-V by securing 25,129 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was PTI-P candidate Habib Ali Shah who bagged 13,917 votes.
Voters turnout remained 39.01 percent.
